An authentic Cape Town dish, this Masala steak Gatsby sandwich will most likely be able to feed two to three people. Gatsby is Cape Town’s sandwich consisting of a soft baguette, stuffed with deliciously spiced steak strips, onions, tomatoes, lettuce and freshly fried chips. The dish is named after F. Scott Fitzgerald’s novel, The Great Gatsby. There are many different ingredients you can use to stuff your sandwich from bacon, sausages, calamari and more. ALSO SEE: Recipe of the day: Cinnamon swirl banana bread *This recipe was found on tastyrecipessapeople.com